userdoc.notice: Smart contract library for advanced fixed-point math. It works with int256 numbers considered to have 18 trailing decimals. We call this number representation signed 59.18-decimal fixed-point, since the numbers can have a sign and there can be up to 59 digits in the integer part and up to 18 decimals in the fractional part. The numbers are bound by the minimum and the maximum values permitted by the Solidity type int256.
